---

DATABASE SCHEMA

Table: products

id (uuid)

designation (string)

normalized_designation (string)

contents (text, nullable)

pack_code (string, nullable)

case_qty (integer, nullable)

price (integer)

source_file (string)

last_updated (timestamp)

---

NORMALIZATION

Convert designation:

lowercase
remove spaces
remove "-", "/", "(", ")"

Example:

3308 A/C3 → 3308ac3
VKTC 0904 → vktc0904

---

PDF PARSING PIPELINE

Step 1: Extract raw text using pdfplumber

Step 2: Split into lines

Step 3: Detect format

---

FORMAT DETECTION LOGIC

If line contains multiple prices in same row:

→ use FORMAT 2 parser

Else:

→ use FORMAT 1 parser

---

FORMAT 1 PARSER

1 detect designation at line start
2 merge multi-line rows
3 extract fields using regex
4 clean values
5 store in DB

---

FORMAT 2 PARSER (CRITICAL)

1 identify rows with TWO entries

Example line:

3308 A/C3 14021    3317 A/C3 76444

2 split line into left and right halves

3 extract:

LEFT:

designation_left
price_left

RIGHT:

designation_right
price_right

4 create TWO DB records

Record 1:

designation = left
price = left price

Record 2:

designation = right
price = right price

5 set missing fields:

contents = null
pack_code = null
case_qty = null

---

OCR FALLBACK

If text extraction fails:

Use pytesseract OCR

Then apply same parsing logic

---

UPSERT RULE

normalized_designation is unique

If exists:

update all details (designation, contents, pack_code, case_qty, price, source_file, last_updated)

If not:

insert new row

---

SEARCH ENGINE

Search must prioritize part numbers.

Steps:

normalize query
remove words like "bearing", "price"

---

SEARCH METHODS

1 exact match
2 partial match
3 fuzzy match

---

FUZZY MATCHING

Use:

PostgreSQL pg_trgm
or RapidFuzz

---

TYPEAHEAD SEARCH

Must support instant suggestions.

Example:

62 → 6200, 6201, 6202

---

VOICE SEARCH

Use Web Speech API in browser

---

API

POST /upload

GET /search?q=

---

PERFORMANCE TARGETS

Search < 100 ms

Parsing < 10 sec per 1000 rows

---

SYSTEM SUMMARY

System supports:

multiple PDF formats
table parsing
dual-column parsing
fuzzy search
voice search

Runs 24/7 on free hosting

Accessible from phone and desktop

